title: Grateful Dead Live at Soldiers' and Sailors' Memorial Hall on 1977-10-28

Promised Land, They Love Each Other, Cassidy, Tennessee Jed, Mexicali Blues-> Big River, Brown Eyed Women, Lazy Lightning-> Supplication, Deal

Set 2

Samson & Delilah, Candyman, Sunrise, Passenger, He's Gone-> Drums-> Not Fade Away-> Stella Blue-> Goin' Down The Road Feelin' Bad-> Around & Around, E: Casey Jones

reviews.review_text:
Good Matrix. Good Show (w/ Qualifications)... ...Both being subject to a good board.  But along with the usual superlatives I like to give the magic makers who make everyone in the community smile, I have to say this show or this mix (I don't know which) runs waayyy too slow.  While I was creating my own custom second set  placing Passenger out front with a segue into Samson, dumping Sunrise to create a really nice transition of Candyman into He's Gone; and lastly splicing  GDTRFB > Casey Jones (which was very tricky doing it clean and natural), I couldn't help noticing the pace of the show was horrible.  There was no life in it at all - truly death-defying.  So I sped it up significantly in Soundforge.  And it sounds much better!  This slow pace could very well be a foreshadowing of the awful show they played on the 30th with the 30th being one of the worst performances I've ever heard.  So be forewarned.  

Jerry is in good voice tonight and does an excellent job on Candyman as well as Stella Blue.  Being fairly scarce, I am always searching for well played and well sung Candymen, Peggy-Os, and High Times.  It's too bad Promised Land is corrupted.  It would have made for a nicely complete first set.   Overall, this is a  show worthy of collecting - if you can clean it up.

hotttt this show is excellent. my only complaint is that i wish keith and bonbys guitar were a bit higher in the mix. otherwise great matrix, great crowd, great performances. awesome night for everyone vocally. fucking excellent night for donna. some great jerry n bobby moments. first set is high energy, second set is pretty up n down, not the super rockinest overall but picks up at the end. its all good, first night of the tour and i dont think id like it if every show had the same energetic contour or was just all high energy. great show, great recording.
